least come very close to Donald
Trump.

29:50.122 --> 29:57.229 align:left position:0%,start line:80% size:100%
That momentum at best has been
stalled. Maybe he's even gone
backwards. But I do agree that

29:57.229 --> 30:01.199 align:left position:0%,start line:73.33% size:100%
we sometimes make too much of
these debates, right? It's not
just the people that are
watching

30:01.199 --> 30:06.271 align:left position:0%,start line:80% size:100%
them. It's a small subset. But
many people in New Hampshire are
doing other things, are

30:06.271 --> 30:07.472 align:left position:0%,start line:93.33% size:100%
thinking about other things.

30:07.472 --> 30:08.407 align:left position:25%,start line:93.33% size:75%
(CROSSTALK)

30:08.407 --> 30:09.741 align:left position:0%,start line:86.67% size:100%
GWEN IFILL: Including the
Super Bowl, perhaps.

30:09.741 --> 30:11.877 align:left position:12.5%,start line:93.33% size:87.5%
AMY WALTER: Perhaps.

30:11.877 --> 30:16.281 align:left position:0%,start line:80% size:100%
And what we think is really
important, this -- or the media
thinks is very important,

30:16.281 --> 30:20.352 align:left position:0%,start line:73.33% size:100%
this idea that he's robotic,
that he never changes his
message, is actually not a
problem

30:20.352 --> 30:24.523 align:left position:0%,start line:80% size:100%
for a candidate. We talk about
candidates needing to be
message-disciplined. Most voters

30:24.523 --> 30:29.895 align:left position:0%,start line:80% size:100%
are spending .000005 percent of
their time hearing politics,
listening to politics. If

30:29.895 --> 30:31.229 align:left position:0%,start line:86.67% size:100%
you say the same message over
and over again, it gets through.

30:31.229 --> 30:31.596 align:left position:0%,start line:93.33% size:100%
GWEN IFILL: That's what sticks.

30:31.596 --> 30:33.298 align:left position:25%,start line:93.33% size:75%
AMY WALTER: Yes.

30:33.298 --> 30:36.201 align:left position:0%,start line:80% size:100%
GWEN IFILL: Well, let's talk
about the larger question,
because you had a good story on

30:36.201 --> 30:42.574 align:left position:0%,start line:80% size:100%
NPR today, Tam, about Trump,
Donald Trump and his similarity
to Bernie Sanders, talking

30:42.574 --> 30:45.444 align:left position:0%,start line:80% size:100%
about message and the things
they actually say and their
appeal, not just how they do

30:45.444 --> 30:46.712 align:left position:25%,start line:93.33% size:75%
in a debate.

30:46.712 --> 30:50.382 align:left position:0%,start line:93.33% size:100%
TAMARA KEITH: Absolutely.

30:50.382 --> 30:55.120 align:left position:0%,start line:73.33% size:100%
And there are many things where
they are nowhere near each
other. Let's just establish
that.

30:55.120 --> 30:59.624 align:left position:0%,start line:80% size:100%
But there are surprising areas
where they overlap, things like
preserving Social Security

30:59.624 --> 31:05.564 align:left position:12.5%,start line:73.33% size:87.5%
or even expanding Social
Security, not cutting Social
Security benefits,
infrastructure,

31:05.564 --> 31:10.068 align:left position:0%,start line:73.33% size:100%
and simply the way they talk
about this feeling that the
American dream is maybe not
within

31:10.068 --> 31:13.605 align:left position:12.5%,start line:86.67% size:87.5%
reach in a way it
was in the past.

31:13.605 --> 31:17.809 align:left position:0%,start line:80% size:100%
They are tapping into many of
the same things and using many
of the same phrases to talk

31:17.809 --> 31:20.679 align:left position:0%,start line:93.33% size:100%
about those things, also trade.

31:20.679 --> 31:24.583 align:left position:0%,start line:73.33% size:100%
GWEN IFILL: Well, let's be
completely clear about
something, and that's that we
don't

31:24.583 --> 31:27.819 align:left position:0%,start line:80% size:100%
know what's going to happen
tomorrow night. As a matter of
fact, Dixville Notch starts

31:27.819 --> 31:32.524 align:left position:0%,start line:86.67% size:100%
voting at midnight. I love
this part of the year.

31:32.524 --> 31:37.095 align:left position:0%,start line:73.33% size:100%
But there is a big expectations
game under way. And 24 hours
out, Amy, what is the
expectations

31:37.095 --> 31:40.198 align:left position:0%,start line:93.33% size:100%
game? How would you sum it up?

31:40.198 --> 31:44.536 align:left position:0%,start line:80% size:100%
AMY WALTER: On the Democratic
side, it's that Bernie Sanders
wins, but by what margin? And

31:44.536 --> 31:48.907 align:left position:0%,start line:80% size:100%
on the Republican side, Trump
wins, again, what margin, and,
more important, what happens

31:48.907 --> 31:55.914 align:left position:0%,start line:80% size:100%
to the non-Trump, non-Cruz
candidates, the Kasich, Rubio,
Bush, Christie?

31:55.914 --> 32:00.685 align:left position:0%,start line:80% size:100%
Will one or more of those
candidates drop out after New
Hampshire, and then the rest

32:00.685 --> 32:03.989 align:left position:12.5%,start line:86.67% size:87.5%
of those folks coalesce
around the one who's left?

32:03.989 --> 32:07.225 align:left position:12.5%,start line:80% size:87.5%
GWEN IFILL: How does the
expectations game feel on the
ground, Tam?

32:07.225 --> 32:14.432 align:left position:0%,start line:80% size:100%
TAMARA KEITH: Well, Ted Cruz
today was actually trying to
lower expectations, which is not

32:14.432 --> 32:16.935 align:left position:0%,start line:73.33% size:100%
something that he did before
Iowa. Of course, this is a very
different state and less
friendly

32:16.935 --> 32:19.905 align:left position:12.5%,start line:93.33% size:87.5%
territory for him.

32:19.905 --> 32:26.044 align:left position:0%,start line:73.33% size:100%
And Hillary Clinton has been for
months saying, well, you know,
Bernie Sanders is from a
neighboring

32:26.044 --> 32:30.849 align:left position:0%,start line:80% size:100%
state. I think that the Clinton
camp is prepared to lose in Iowa
-- is prepared to lose here

32:30.849 --> 32:36.421 align:left position:0%,start line:80% size:100%
in New Hampshire. It's not clear
how much that will be by. And
also Bernie Sanders is

32:36.421 --> 32:40.559 align:left position:0%,start line:80% size:100%
also tempering expectations,
saying, you know, New Hampshire
has been very friendly to the

32:40.559 --> 32:44.095 align:left position:0%,start line:86.67% size:100%
Clintons. I think nobody wants
to lose the expectations game.

32:44.095 --> 32:47.833 align:left position:12.5%,start line:80% size:87.5%
GWEN IFILL: And they're
perfectly aware of how volatile
last-minute voting is in New

32:47.833 --> 32:49.668 align:left position:25%,start line:93.33% size:75%
Hampshire.

32:49.668 --> 32:53.605 align:left position:0%,start line:80% size:100%
Tamara Keith, get out with those
voters. Amy Walter, start
reading those exit polls. And

32:53.605 --> 32:57.442 align:left position:12.5%,start line:86.67% size:87.5%
we will talk to you
both tomorrow night.

32:57.442 --> 33:03.281 align:left position:0%,start line:73.33% size:100%
Tune in on Thursday night at
9:00 p.m. Eastern, when Judy and
I host a "PBS NewsHour"
Democratic

33:03.281 --> 33:13.725 align:left position:12.5%,start line:73.33% size:87.5%
presidential debate in
partnership with Facebook from
the University of Wisconsin,
Milwaukee.

33:13.725 --> 33:24.636 align:left position:0%,start line:73.33% size:100%
JUDY WOODRUFF: Now to the
growing effort to rein in the
mosquito-borne Zika virus
spreading

33:24.636 --> 33:30.175 align:left position:0%,start line:80% size:100%
through parts of South and
Central America. It is suspected
of being the cause devastating

33:30.175 --> 33:35.447 align:left position:0%,start line:80% size:100%
birth defects in children who
are born to women who become
infected during pregnancy.

33:35.447 --> 33:39.718 align:left position:0%,start line:80% size:100%
Our science correspondent, Miles
O'Brien, has been reporting on
developments from Brazil,

33:39.718 --> 33:42.888 align:left position:25%,start line:86.67% size:75%
which has been
hard-hit by the virus.

33:42.888 --> 33:48.727 align:left position:0%,start line:73.33% size:100%
Tonight, he looks at ways
doctors and scientists are
racing to get ahead of the
outbreak.

33:48.727 --> 33:56.067 align:left position:0%,start line:80% size:100%
MILES O'BRIEN: It's Carnival
week in Brazil, the raucous
run-up to Lent, when people take

33:56.067 --> 34:02.540 align:left position:0%,start line:80% size:100%
to the streets to party their
worries away. But this year,
it's harder to mask reality,

34:02.540 --> 34:06.578 align:left position:0%,start line:86.67% size:100%
as a frightening epidemic also
marches through the nation.

34:06.578 --> 34:10.615 align:left position:12.5%,start line:73.33% size:87.5%
DR. ADRIANA SCAVUZZI,
Obstetrician: They come to us
asking many questions, and we
cannot

34:10.615 --> 34:16.288 align:left position:0%,start line:80% size:100%
say almost nothing with 100
percent sure. What we have to do
is to support them. That's

34:16.288 --> 34:19.157 align:left position:12.5%,start line:93.33% size:87.5%
all we have to do.

34:19.157 --> 34:23.528 align:left position:0%,start line:80% size:100%
MILES O'BRIEN: Dr. Adriana
Scavuzzi is an obstetrician at
one of the largest hospitals

34:23.528 --> 34:29.434 align:left position:0%,start line:80% size:100%
in Recife, the epicenter of a
fast-moving outbreak of the Zika
virus, a flavivirus virus

34:29.434 --> 34:34.773 align:left position:0%,start line:86.67% size:100%
in the same family as yellow
fever, West Nile and dengue.

34:34.773 --> 34:40.679 align:left position:12.5%,start line:73.33% size:87.5%
In each case, the virus
hitchhikes on a tenacious
day-biting mosquito called Aedes
aegypti that

34:40.679 --> 34:48.586 align:left position:0%,start line:80% size:100%
has origins in Africa and is now
spreading throughout the globe.
Two-month-old Nicollas

34:48.586 --> 34:53.558 align:left position:0%,start line:86.67% size:100%
(ph) Pereira has an abnormally
small head, microcephaly.

34:53.558 --> 34:57.696 align:left position:0%,start line:80% size:100%
Doctors at this hospital would
normally see 10 cases like this
a year. But starting in

34:57.696 --> 35:03.802 align:left position:12.5%,start line:86.67% size:87.5%
August, there were
suddenly 10 to 20 a month.

35:03.802 --> 35:08.673 align:left position:0%,start line:73.33% size:100%
Dr. Ana Van Der Linden is a
pediatric neurologist. She says
Nicollas must contend with an
array

35:08.673 --> 35:12.410 align:left position:12.5%,start line:86.67% size:87.5%
of permanent mental and
physical problems.

35:12.410 --> 35:16.147 align:left position:12.5%,start line:73.33% size:87.5%
DR. ANA VAN DER LINDEN,
Pediatric Neurologist (through
translator): With this
impairment,

35:16.147 --> 35:21.186 align:left position:0%,start line:80% size:100%
we see that reflex reactions are
good, but voluntary actions that
depend on better brain

35:21.186 --> 35:26.624 align:left position:0%,start line:80% size:100%
development will be impaired. He
will have bad motor skills and
mental development. He

35:26.624 --> 35:31.596 align:left position:0%,start line:80% size:100%
can also have abnormal vision,
hearing disorders and bone
malformation.

35:31.596 --> 35:38.236 align:left position:0%,start line:80% size:100%
MILES O'BRIEN: His mother,
Elizangela, says she developed a
rash while she was pregnant.

35:38.236 --> 35:43.274 align:left position:0%,start line:80% size:100%
As it turns out, she had the
Zika virus, apparently after a
mosquito bite.

35:43.274 --> 35:47.345 align:left position:0%,start line:80% size:100%
ELIZANGELA PEREIRA, Mother
(through translator): Sometimes,
I worry. Sometimes, I wonder if

35:47.345 --> 35:53.151 align:left position:0%,start line:80% size:100%
he will survive, but I always
believe that God will help. My
only fear is losing him.

35:53.151 --> 35:55.954 align:left position:12.5%,start line:93.33% size:87.5%
But I'm at peace.

35:55.954 --> 36:01.359 align:left position:0%,start line:80% size:100%
MILES O'BRIEN: Elizangela's
personal tragedy is part of an
unprecedented global mystery.

36:01.359 --> 36:02.927 align:left position:0%,start line:80% size:100%
DR. LAURA RODRIGUES, London
School of Hygiene and Tropical
Medicine: I think this is one

36:02.927 --> 36:09.100 align:left position:12.5%,start line:80% size:87.5%
of the most unexpected
epidemiological situations,
maybe in decades.

36:09.100 --> 36:14.806 align:left position:0%,start line:73.33% size:100%
MILES O'BRIEN: Laura Rodrigues
is an epidemiologist with the
London School of Hygiene and
Tropical

36:14.806 --> 36:22.113 align:left position:0%,start line:80% size:100%
Medicine who raced to her home
country to help answer some
questions in a hurry.

36:22.113 --> 36:26.151 align:left position:12.5%,start line:80% size:87.5%
Even the numbers are a
challenge. Brazilian government
health workers are investigating

36:26.151 --> 36:31.623 align:left position:12.5%,start line:80% size:87.5%
more than four thousand
suspected microcephaly cases
that might be linked to Zika.

36:31.623 --> 36:34.692 align:left position:0%,start line:80% size:100%
DR. LAURA RODRIGUES: There is so
much we don't know, and one of
the things we don't know

36:34.692 --> 36:39.697 align:left position:0%,start line:80% size:100%
is exactly how many babies are
affected. Right now, there are
pregnant women being exposed

36:39.697 --> 36:42.901 align:left position:0%,start line:86.67% size:100%
and possibly infected. It's
very difficult to predict.

36:42.901 --> 36:49.274 align:left position:0%,start line:80% size:100%
MILES O'BRIEN: Zika's enigmatic
history offers us few clues. It
was first isolated in Uganda

36:49.274 --> 36:56.581 align:left position:0%,start line:80% size:100%
in 1947. It circulated in Africa
and a broad stretch of Asia,
then popped up in the Pacific

36:56.581 --> 37:05.957 align:left position:0%,start line:73.33% size:100%
in 2007. The biggest outbreak,
in 2013, was in French
Polynesia, an estimated 19,000
cases.

37:05.957 --> 37:10.628 align:left position:0%,start line:73.33% size:100%
But over the years, no one paid
a lot of attention to Zika
because the symptoms are
generally

37:10.628 --> 37:14.833 align:left position:0%,start line:80% size:100%
mild. In fact, four out of five
never know they have it. No one
is sure why it took such

37:14.833 --> 37:17.368 align:left position:25%,start line:93.33% size:75%
a vicious turn.

37:17.368 --> 37:21.573 align:left position:0%,start line:80% size:100%
DR. LAURA RODRIGUES: It could be
biogenetic mutation of the
virus, and it could be that

37:21.573 --> 37:27.812 align:left position:0%,start line:80% size:100%
just once they escaped Africa
and got into urban, very densely
populated areas, it was

37:27.812 --> 37:31.416 align:left position:0%,start line:80% size:100%
easier to transmit, or it could
be something else, the mosquito
maybe. It's all happening

37:31.416 --> 37:33.952 align:left position:25%,start line:93.33% size:75%
very, very fast.

37:33.952 --> 37:39.224 align:left position:0%,start line:80% size:100%
MILES O'BRIEN: Making a smoking
gun connection between Zika in
mothers and microcephaly in

37:39.224 --> 37:43.128 align:left position:0%,start line:86.67% size:100%
their unborn children is a
challenge for scientists.

37:43.128 --> 37:49.634 align:left position:12.5%,start line:80% size:87.5%
By the time infants are
diagnosed, the virus is usually
long gone. But here in Recife,

37:49.634 --> 37:55.473 align:left position:0%,start line:80% size:100%
the case grew stronger last
week. At this government lab,
researchers used a new test

37:55.473 --> 38:01.713 align:left position:0%,start line:80% size:100%
and found Zika antibodies in the
spinal fluid of 12 babies with
microcephaly, meaning the

38:01.713 --> 38:06.217 align:left position:0%,start line:80% size:100%
virus can reach the baby's
nervous system and brain in
utero. Researchers believe the

38:06.217 --> 38:10.054 align:left position:0%,start line:86.67% size:100%
virus targets nerve cells
as a fetus develops.

38:10.054 --> 38:13.558 align:left position:0%,start line:86.67% size:100%
RAFAEL FRANCA, Immunologist: So
this is where we keep the virus.

38:13.558 --> 38:19.130 align:left position:0%,start line:73.33% size:100%
MILES O'BRIEN: Rafael Franca
(ph) is an immunologist here. He
showed me the deep freeze where
they

38:19.130 --> 38:23.668 align:left position:0%,start line:73.33% size:100%
keep the Zika samples for
research that will lay the
groundwork for a better
diagnostic

38:23.668 --> 38:27.739 align:left position:0%,start line:86.67% size:100%
test, therapies and maybe
one day a vaccine.

38:27.739 --> 38:32.477 align:left position:0%,start line:80% size:100%
RAFAEL FRANCA: I cannot say that
we have the situation under
control. I believe now the

38:32.477 --> 38:37.515 align:left position:0%,start line:80% size:100%
only way to control virus'
spreading is to eliminate the
vector.

38:37.515 --> 38:43.388 align:left position:0%,start line:80% size:100%
MILES O'BRIEN: That vector is
the mosquito. In nearly every
case, Zika is transmitted

38:43.388 --> 38:47.192 align:left position:12.5%,start line:73.33% size:87.5%
by a mosquito bite. The
Brazilian government has
deployed nearly 250,000 troops
to wage

38:47.192 --> 38:51.095 align:left position:12.5%,start line:93.33% size:87.5%
war with the insects.

38:51.095 --> 38:55.333 align:left position:12.5%,start line:73.33% size:87.5%
They have been spraying
insecticides and adding
larvicides to standing water
where mosquitoes

38:55.333 --> 38:57.735 align:left position:25%,start line:93.33% size:75%
lay their eggs.

38:57.735 --> 39:01.706 align:left position:0%,start line:86.67% size:100%
Gaspar Canuto is a Recife
government health worker.

39:01.706 --> 39:05.677 align:left position:0%,start line:86.67% size:100%
How much of this is to show the
public you are doing something?

39:05.677 --> 39:08.680 align:left position:0%,start line:80% size:100%
GASPAR CANUTO, Public Health
Worker (through translator): One
hundred percent of this action

39:08.680 --> 39:13.751 align:left position:12.5%,start line:80% size:87.5%
is aiming to reduce the
incidence of mosquitoes and also
of the disease.

39:13.751 --> 39:18.957 align:left position:0%,start line:73.33% size:100%
MILES O'BRIEN: Efforts like
this, while well-intentioned,
seem unlikely to stop the
outbreak anytime

39:18.957 --> 39:25.129 align:left position:0%,start line:80% size:100%
soon in Brazil or in other
countries hit by Zika,
especially in Latin America.

39:25.129 --> 39:30.768 align:left position:0%,start line:80% size:100%
The scale of this is pretty
mind-boggling. A single female
mosquito in her short lifetime

39:30.768 --> 39:35.673 align:left position:0%,start line:80% size:100%
will lay hundreds of eggs. And
she's looking for a place like
this, standing water, not

39:35.673 --> 39:39.911 align:left position:0%,start line:80% size:100%
much more than a puddle. But
what is really interesting is,
that's about al the water

39:39.911 --> 39:42.313 align:left position:25%,start line:93.33% size:75%
she needs.

39:42.313 --> 39:47.252 align:left position:0%,start line:80% size:100%
With all this in mind, the
Brazilian government is warning
citizens that standing water can

39:47.252 --> 39:52.490 align:left position:0%,start line:80% size:100%
be dangerous. But in this slum
in Recife, there is no running
water.

39:52.490 --> 39:57.061 align:left position:0%,start line:80% size:100%
DR. ADRIANA SCAVUZZI: Can you
imagine a family that they don't
have even tap water? They

39:57.061 --> 40:02.867 align:left position:0%,start line:73.33% size:100%
have to keep water in the
containers. So it makes the
perfect environment for the
mosquito.

40:02.867 --> 40:09.540 align:left position:0%,start line:80% size:100%
To try to solve the medical
problem won't be enough. You
have to change the quality

40:09.540 --> 40:15.113 align:left position:0%,start line:86.67% size:100%
of people's life. Otherwise, you
will not solve this problem.

40:15.113 --> 40:21.252 align:left position:0%,start line:80% size:100%
MILES O'BRIEN: Doctors here say
the biggest frustration is they
can't fix what ails these

40:21.252 --> 40:27.458 align:left position:0%,start line:73.33% size:100%
babies, all because of a single
mosquito bite. It has
dramatically changed
Elizangela's life.

40:27.458 --> 40:31.229 align:left position:0%,start line:80% size:100%
She had to quit her job as a
farmworker to care for little
Nicollas.

40:31.229 --> 40:34.465 align:left position:0%,start line:80% size:100%
ELIZANGELA PEREIRA (through
translator): I think I will be
here at the hospital forever.

40:34.465 --> 40:38.870 align:left position:0%,start line:80% size:100%
I do not know if he will be able
to walk. I don't know, but I
believe that God will

40:38.870 --> 40:41.472 align:left position:37.5%,start line:93.33% size:62.5%
help me.

40:41.472 --> 40:48.012 align:left position:0%,start line:80% size:100%
MILES O'BRIEN: One woman's sad,
but hopeful prayer this Carnival
season. It's still a

40:48.012 --> 40:52.517 align:left position:0%,start line:80% size:100%
time to try and forget your
troubles, but in Brazil this
year, a steady drumbeat of

40:52.517 --> 40:56.921 align:left position:25%,start line:86.67% size:75%
worry seems
impossible to ignore.

40:56.921 --> 41:10.101 align:left position:12.5%,start line:86.67% size:87.5%
Miles O'Brien, the "PBS
NewsHour," Recife, Brazil.

41:10.101 --> 41:19.377 align:left position:12.5%,start line:80% size:87.5%
GWEN IFILL: It's been a
generation since the Cold War
ended, a standoff that dominated

41:19.377 --> 41:22.647 align:left position:0%,start line:93.33% size:100%
much of the 20th century.

41:22.647 --> 41:27.185 align:left position:0%,start line:80% size:100%
But now echoes of that conflict
are sounding again, as the U.S.
and its allies encounter

41:27.185 --> 41:29.687 align:left position:12.5%,start line:93.33% size:87.5%
a resurgent Russia.

41:29.687 --> 41:33.758 align:left position:12.5%,start line:80% size:87.5%
Chief foreign affairs
correspondent Margaret Warner
reports.

41:33.758 --> 41:38.796 align:left position:12.5%,start line:73.33% size:87.5%
MARGARET WARNER: NATO is
planning its biggest buildup in
Eastern Europe since the Cold
War,

41:38.796 --> 41:41.999 align:left position:12.5%,start line:86.67% size:87.5%
all to deter a newly
assertive Russia.

41:41.999 --> 41:44.669 align:left position:0%,start line:80% size:100%
ASHTON CARTER, U.S. Defense
Secretary: We haven't had to
worry about this for 25 years.

41:44.669 --> 41:48.906 align:left position:12.5%,start line:86.67% size:87.5%
And while I wish it were
otherwise, now we do.

41:48.906 --> 41:53.311 align:left position:0%,start line:73.33% size:100%
MARGARET WARNER: Last week,
Defense Secretary Ash Carter
proposed to quadruple U.S.
spending

41:53.311 --> 41:57.815 align:left position:0%,start line:80% size:100%
on its -- quote -- "European
reassurance initiative" to $3.4
billion.

41:57.815 --> 42:03.955 align:left position:0%,start line:80% size:100%
ASHTON CARTER: That will fund a
lot of things: more rotational
U.S. forces in Europe, more

42:03.955 --> 42:08.659 align:left position:0%,start line:73.33% size:100%
training and exercising with our
allies, more prepositioned
war-fighting gear and
infrastructure

42:08.659 --> 42:11.596 align:left position:25%,start line:86.67% size:75%
improvements to
support all this.

42:11.596 --> 42:15.366 align:left position:0%,start line:73.33% size:100%
MARGARET WARNER: This week in
Brussels, NATO's defense
ministers will discuss setting
up

42:15.366 --> 42:21.973 align:left position:0%,start line:80% size:100%
outposts along its eastern front
to do just that. But is this
wise or necessary?

42:21.973 --> 42:25.376 align:left position:0%,start line:80% size:100%
Evelyn Farkas just left her post
as assistant secretary of
defense for Russia, Ukraine and

42:25.376 --> 42:27.311 align:left position:37.5%,start line:93.33% size:62.5%
Eurasia.

42:27.311 --> 42:30.715 align:left position:0%,start line:73.33% size:100%
EVELYN FARKAS, Former Defense
Department Official: This is
something that we absolutely
need

42:30.715 --> 42:34.986 align:left position:0%,start line:80% size:100%
to do. It is a sign of our
resolve. It's a sign that the
United States is there with

42:34.986 --> 42:39.490 align:left position:0%,start line:80% size:100%
our NATO allies, that we're
there also to send a signal to
Russia. I mean, it's clearly

42:39.490 --> 42:41.993 align:left position:12.5%,start line:93.33% size:87.5%
a deterrent effort.

42:41.993 --> 42:47.932 align:left position:0%,start line:73.33% size:100%
MARGARET WARNER: But Jack
Matlock, ambassador to the
Soviet Union from 1987 to 1991,
warns

42:47.932 --> 42:53.638 align:left position:0%,start line:80% size:100%
it will simply provoke Russian
leader Vladimir Putin into
further aggressive moves.

42:53.638 --> 42:57.175 align:left position:0%,start line:80% size:100%
JACK MATLOCK, Former U.S.
Ambassador to the Soviet Union:
I think it's a bad idea. I think

42:57.175 --> 43:05.149 align:left position:0%,start line:80% size:100%
it's not necessary. I think it's
going to lead to even more
confrontation with Russia.

43:05.149 --> 43:13.090 align:left position:0%,start line:80% size:100%
And, probably, simply they will
move more of their military
equipment to the border.

43:13.090 --> 43:17.261 align:left position:0%,start line:80% size:100%
MARGARET WARNER: Estonia's
ambassador to the U.S., Eerik
Marmei, echoes all three Baltic

43:17.261 --> 43:20.331 align:left position:0%,start line:86.67% size:100%
nations in insisting they
need the protection.

43:20.331 --> 43:25.069 align:left position:12.5%,start line:73.33% size:87.5%
EERIK MARMEI, Estonian
Ambassador to the United States:
It a very clear sign of the U.S.
commitment

43:25.069 --> 43:31.075 align:left position:0%,start line:73.33% size:100%
to enhance the deterrence in
Europe, and especially in the
eastern part of Europe in the
coming

43:31.075 --> 43:31.909 align:left position:37.5%,start line:93.33% size:62.5%
years.

43:31.909 --> 43:33.978 align:left position:12.5%,start line:86.67% size:87.5%
MARGARET WARNER: Why
do you need more?

43:33.978 --> 43:40.852 align:left position:0%,start line:80% size:100%
EERIK MARMEI: What we have seen
in recent years is the change of
security environment

43:40.852 --> 43:47.358 align:left position:0%,start line:73.33% size:100%
in Europe. We have seen that
Russia has violated main
principles of international
agreements,

43:47.358 --> 43:50.194 align:left position:37.5%,start line:93.33% size:62.5%
law.

43:50.194 --> 43:58.035 align:left position:0%,start line:80% size:100%
MARGARET WARNER: He's referring
to Russia's 2008 invasion of the
former Republic of Georgia,

43:58.035 --> 44:02.340 align:left position:0%,start line:80% size:100%
capturing two pro-Russian
territories. It triggered the
deepest rift between Russia

44:02.340 --> 44:06.611 align:left position:12.5%,start line:86.67% size:87.5%
and the West since the
fall of the Soviet Union.

44:06.611 --> 44:11.382 align:left position:0%,start line:80% size:100%
Tensions exploded anew in 2014,
when Russia invaded and annexed
the Crimean Peninsula

44:11.382 --> 44:15.253 align:left position:12.5%,start line:86.67% size:87.5%
of the former Soviet
Republic of Ukraine.

44:15.253 --> 44:19.323 align:left position:12.5%,start line:80% size:87.5%
VLADIMIR PUTIN, Russian
President (through translator):
This strategic territory should

44:19.323 --> 44:24.595 align:left position:0%,start line:80% size:100%
be under strong and stable
sovereignty, which, in fact,
could be today only Russian.

44:24.595 --> 44:29.233 align:left position:0%,start line:73.33% size:100%
MARGARET WARNER: The Kremlin
then provoked war in mainland
Ukraine's East between
pro-Russian

44:29.233 --> 44:36.107 align:left position:0%,start line:80% size:100%
separatists and government
forces. With more than 9,000
dead, the conflict continues.

44:36.107 --> 44:41.846 align:left position:0%,start line:73.33% size:100%
Also sounding alarms in the
West, Russia's recent
multibillion-dollar military
buildup,

44:41.846 --> 44:48.753 align:left position:12.5%,start line:73.33% size:87.5%
with large-scale ground
exercises, overflights of
neighbors and a spike in
submarine activity.

44:48.753 --> 44:53.090 align:left position:0%,start line:80% size:100%
NATO's commander in Europe, U.S.
General Philip Breedlove, has
issued repeated warnings.

44:53.090 --> 44:55.259 align:left position:0%,start line:80% size:100%
GEN. PHILIP BREEDLOVE, NATO
Supreme Allied Commander: Russia
is blatantly attempting

44:55.259 --> 44:59.830 align:left position:12.5%,start line:73.33% size:87.5%
to change the rules and
principles that have been the
foundation of European security
for

44:59.830 --> 45:01.933 align:left position:37.5%,start line:93.33% size:62.5%
decades.

45:01.933 --> 45:07.572 align:left position:0%,start line:80% size:100%
MARGARET WARNER: But how far do
Putin's ambitions extend? It's
one thing to reassert influence

45:07.572 --> 45:13.311 align:left position:0%,start line:80% size:100%
in former Soviet republics, like
Ukraine, Georgia and Moldova.
But would he really move

45:13.311 --> 45:17.815 align:left position:12.5%,start line:80% size:87.5%
against once independent
countries the Soviets took over
during World War II who are now

45:17.815 --> 45:21.218 align:left position:12.5%,start line:86.67% size:87.5%
free members of the
NATO alliance?

45:21.218 --> 45:25.623 align:left position:0%,start line:73.33% size:100%
NARRATOR: This union of 12
nations became known as the
North Atlantic Treaty
Organization,

45:25.623 --> 45:28.960 align:left position:12.5%,start line:93.33% size:87.5%
or, more simply, NATO.

45:28.960 --> 45:35.099 align:left position:0%,start line:80% size:100%
MARGARET WARNER: NATO was formed
in April 1949 with 12 members to
defend themselves

45:35.099 --> 45:41.439 align:left position:0%,start line:80% size:100%
from the Soviet Union based on
the principle of an attack on
one is an attack on all.

45:41.439 --> 45:48.012 align:left position:0%,start line:80% size:100%
But after the Berlin Wall fell
in 1989 and the Soviet Union
collapsed in 1991, many former

45:48.012 --> 45:53.985 align:left position:0%,start line:80% size:100%
Soviet satellite states and
Republicans sought and won the
protection of NATO's security

45:53.985 --> 46:01.058 align:left position:0%,start line:73.33% size:100%
umbrella. Most galling to the
Russians was NATO's 2004
incorporation of three tiny
Baltic

46:01.058 --> 46:03.928 align:left position:12.5%,start line:73.33% size:87.5%
states, former Soviet
Republicans where many ethnic
Russians still live, Lithuania,
Latvia,

46:03.928 --> 46:06.063 align:left position:25%,start line:93.33% size:75%
and Estonia.

46:06.063 --> 46:09.033 align:left position:0%,start line:80% size:100%
BARACK OBAMA, President of the
United States: We will defend
our NATO allies, and that means

46:09.033 --> 46:11.369 align:left position:25%,start line:93.33% size:75%
every ally.

46:11.369 --> 46:16.040 align:left position:0%,start line:80% size:100%
MARGARET WARNER: In September
2014, after the Ukraine crisis
erupted, President Obama

46:16.040 --> 46:21.145 align:left position:0%,start line:80% size:100%
went to Estonia to reassure the
Baltics and to warn the
Russians.

46:21.145 --> 46:24.915 align:left position:0%,start line:80% size:100%
BARACK OBAMA: So, if, in such a
moment, you ever ask again, who
will come to help, you

46:24.915 --> 46:27.852 align:left position:12.5%,start line:86.67% size:87.5%
will know the answer,
the NATO alliance.

46:27.852 --> 46:31.956 align:left position:0%,start line:80% size:100%
MARGARET WARNER: But is Russia
actually a threat to its Baltic
neighbors?

46:31.956 --> 46:37.361 align:left position:0%,start line:80% size:100%
EVELYN FARKAS: Absolutely.
Absolutely. You know, all of the
countries on Russia's periphery

46:37.361 --> 46:42.933 align:left position:0%,start line:80% size:100%
have been either invaded by
Russia and occupied. The Russian
government, this Kremlin has a

46:42.933 --> 46:47.471 align:left position:0%,start line:80% size:100%
foreign policy that essentially
asserts their right to have
political and economic control

46:47.471 --> 46:49.340 align:left position:12.5%,start line:93.33% size:87.5%
over their periphery.

46:49.340 --> 46:53.277 align:left position:0%,start line:80% size:100%
MARGARET WARNER: What do you
assess is Putin's intention
vis-a-vis these countries?

46:53.277 --> 46:57.081 align:left position:0%,start line:80% size:100%
EVELYN FARKAS: Regionally, he
wants to maintain this political
and economic control. It doesn't

46:57.081 --> 47:00.084 align:left position:0%,start line:80% size:100%
mean he has to invade every
country. He can also try to
undermine the countries through

47:00.084 --> 47:02.520 align:left position:25%,start line:93.33% size:75%
other means.

47:02.520 --> 47:06.857 align:left position:0%,start line:73.33% size:100%
JACK MATLOCK: I don't think
there's any possibility of
Russia making an incursion in
the Baltic

47:06.857 --> 47:08.859 align:left position:37.5%,start line:93.33% size:62.5%
states.

47:08.859 --> 47:12.263 align:left position:12.5%,start line:73.33% size:87.5%
MARGARET WARNER: Former
Ambassador Matlock says the
Russians are simply responding
to

47:12.263 --> 47:17.535 align:left position:0%,start line:80% size:100%
what they see as NATO squeezing
them by expanding right up to
the Russian border.

47:17.535 --> 47:22.440 align:left position:0%,start line:73.33% size:100%
JACK MATLOCK: In their eyes,
they have not committed
aggression, that they are
responding

47:22.440 --> 47:27.778 align:left position:0%,start line:80% size:100%
to aggression from the West, and
particularly from the United
States, which they accuse,

47:27.778 --> 47:34.752 align:left position:0%,start line:80% size:100%
I think unfairly, but sincerely,
of trying to encircle them with
military bases.

47:34.752 --> 47:39.123 align:left position:0%,start line:80% size:100%
MARGARET WARNER: Western leaders
concede they have little insight
into what drives Putin

47:39.123 --> 47:45.029 align:left position:0%,start line:80% size:100%
or what he intends. But mutual
hostility is growing and,
Matlock warns, dangerous.

47:45.029 --> 47:51.502 align:left position:0%,start line:80% size:100%
JACK MATLOCK: There has been
created a almost Cold War
atmosphere of hostility. In that

47:51.502 --> 48:01.545 align:left position:0%,start line:80% size:100%
atmosphere, you are going to
make it very difficult to
cooperate on bigger issues.

48:01.545 --> 48:05.282 align:left position:0%,start line:80% size:100%
MARGARET WARNER: For example, he
says, battling Islamic State
terrorism. And then there's

48:05.282 --> 48:08.385 align:left position:12.5%,start line:86.67% size:87.5%
the nuclear threat
between two superpowers.

48:08.385 --> 48:12.757 align:left position:0%,start line:80% size:100%
JACK MATLOCK: It would be a
catastrophe to get into a war
with Russia. And it seems to

48:12.757 --> 48:17.394 align:left position:12.5%,start line:86.67% size:87.5%
me that you need to deal
with a certain prudence.

48:17.394 --> 48:22.299 align:left position:0%,start line:80% size:100%
MARGARET WARNER: Do you think
that we are sliding into some
kind of new Cold War in

48:22.299 --> 48:26.203 align:left position:0%,start line:80% size:100%
our relationship with Russia?
Should it make us tread more
carefully?

48:26.203 --> 48:32.877 align:left position:0%,start line:80% size:100%
EVELYN FARKAS: Not necessarily.
I mean, we should always tread
carefully, but if by that

48:32.877 --> 48:36.881 align:left position:0%,start line:80% size:100%
you mean that we shouldn't
signal resolve to Russia, I
would say no. We have to signal

48:36.881 --> 48:39.216 align:left position:12.5%,start line:93.33% size:87.5%
resolve to Russia.

48:39.216 --> 48:43.020 align:left position:0%,start line:80% size:100%
MARGARET WARNER: The next signal
of that resolve should come in
Brussels later this week.

48:43.020 --> 48:55.065 align:left position:0%,start line:86.67% size:100%
In Washington, I'm Margaret
Warner for the "PBS NewsHour."

48:55.065 --> 49:08.179 align:left position:0%,start line:80% size:100%
JUDY WOODRUFF: Later tonight on
PBS, a new documentary from
"Independent Lens" showcases

49:08.179 --> 49:15.319 align:left position:12.5%,start line:80% size:87.5%
Misty Copeland the first
African-American woman to be
named principal dancer at New

49:15.319 --> 49:19.056 align:left position:0%,start line:73.33% size:100%
York City's American Ballet
Theater, one of the country's
most prestigious dance
companies.

49:19.056 --> 49:22.159 align:left position:12.5%,start line:93.33% size:87.5%
Here's a preview.

49:22.159 --> 49:30.067 align:left position:0%,start line:80% size:100%
MISTY COPELAND, Ballerina: It
all kind of hit me at once,
moving to New York, realizing

49:30.067 --> 49:35.940 align:left position:0%,start line:80% size:100%
I was the only African-American
woman in a company of 80
dancers.

49:35.940 --> 50:00.064 align:left position:0%,start line:80% size:100%
I felt like I was sinking for a
while. I felt alone in a world
that had become my home.

50:00.064 --> 50:06.904 align:left position:0%,start line:73.33% size:100%
There's just generations of
white girls who can see
themselves as ballerinas. It's,
like,

50:06.904 --> 50:13.177 align:left position:0%,start line:73.33% size:100%
not even a question, because
everyone looks like them on
stage. And it's like this
psychological

50:13.177 --> 50:15.679 align:left position:0%,start line:80% size:100%
thing where, you know, we don't
see ourselves up there, so it's
not something we think we

50:15.679 --> 50:30.461 align:left position:25%,start line:93.33% size:75%
can even dream.

50:30.461 --> 50:37.268 align:left position:0%,start line:73.33% size:100%
I think people think that,
sometimes, I focus too much on
the fact that I'm a black
dancer.

50:37.268 --> 50:41.538 align:left position:0%,start line:73.33% size:100%
I have heard it from, you know,
former principal dancers in
major ballet companies, who
complain

50:41.538 --> 50:47.778 align:left position:0%,start line:93.33% size:100%
about my presence and my voice.

50:47.778 --> 50:58.222 align:left position:0%,start line:73.33% size:100%
I don't think that people
realize what a feat it is being
a black woman. But that's so
much

50:58.222 --> 51:28.285 align:left position:0%,start line:86.67% size:100%
of who I am, and I think it's
so much a part of my story.

51:28.285 --> 51:29.920 align:left position:12.5%,start line:86.67% size:87.5%
JUDY WOODRUFF: Wow.
That's something.

